@@TJvXPCustomWinXPBar.Rolling
Summary
  Indicates whether the control is currently in the process of collapsing or expanding.
Description
  Read Rolling to determine if the control is currently in the transition from expanded to collapsed
  state or the other way around. Rolling is used mainly to avoid re-entrancy problems and infinite
  loops in code.
See Also
  TJvXPCustomWinXPBar.Collapsed

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomWinXPBar.RollMode
Summary
  Specifies how expanding and collapsing the control is performed.
Description
  Use RollMode to control how the control is expanded and collapsed when the Collapsed property changes
  or the user clicks the RollButton. If RollMode is rmFixed, the control is expanded and collapsed a
  fixed amount of pixels (using RollOffset) at each step. If RollMode is rmShrink, the control is
  expanded and collapsed proportionally to the current size of the control.
See Also
  TJvXPCustomWinXPBar.RollOffset, TJvXPCustomWinXPBar.RollStep

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomWinXPBar.RollOffset
Summary
  Indicates how much the control is expanded at each step.
Description
  Use RollOffset to specify how many pixels the control is expanded or collapsed at each step when
  transitioning from expanded to collapsed (or back). A higher value of RollOffset will make the
  control expand and collapse faster but will also make the transition jerkier.
See Also
  TJvXPCustomWinXPBar.RollMode, TJvXPCustomWinXPBar.RollStep

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvXPCustomWinXPBar.RollStep
Summary
  Indicates the number of discreet steps used to collapse and expand the control.
Description
  Set RollStep to specify how smooth the transition from the expanded to the collapsed state is. A
  higher value of RollSteps makes the transition appear smooth but will also take longer.
See Also
  TJvXPCustomWinXPBar.RollMode, TJvXPCustomWinXPBar.RollOffset

